    "answer_id" : 22808112,
    "question_id" : 22807912,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java 8 introduces the possibility to <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se8/html/jls-15.html#jls-15.16\">cast an object to an intersection of types by adding multiple bounds</a>. In the case of serialization, it is therefore possible to write:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Runnable r = (Runnable &amp; Serializable)() -&gt; System.out.println(\"Serializable!\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And the lambda automagically becomes serializable.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 2707688,
